page.title: 14CLUBS SWIMMING FOOTBALL
page.content: I (Scott) train six times a week with five coaches who make me improve my {swimming}for competitions. I have 20 gold medals, 10 silver and 8 bronze, as well as 6 trophies. In my swimming club we can buy different sorts of equipment such as track suits, swimming trunks, bags, hats, jumpers and T-shirts. I practise butterfly, backstroke, free style and breast- stroke. My favourite stroke is the butterfly. The club I belong to is called the Otters. We (Tim and Simon) both play for {football}teams. Tim plays for the school as centre back and Simon for Bearwood as goalie. Tim practises on Mondays after school. The school team has played against three other schools. They won two and lost one. Simon's team were runners up in two leagues and winners of a third.
